  "prompt": "I am using Quora app. I need to answer the question as anonymous. How to do it?",
  "response": "To answer a question anonymously on the Quora app, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open the Quora App**: Launch the Quora app on your device and log in to your account if you aren\u2019t already.\n\n2. **Find the Question**: Navigate to the question you want to answer.\n\n3. **Tap \"Answer\"**: Below the question, tap the \"Answer\" button.\n\n4. **Tap the Gear Icon**: At the top-right corner of the answer draft screen, you\u2019ll see a gear icon (settings). Tap on it.\n\n5. **Enable Anonymous Answer**: Toggle the switch for \"Post Anonymously\" to turn it on. A pop-up will appear to confirm that you want to post anonymously. Tap \"OK.\"\n\n6. **Compose Your Answer**: Write your answer as usual.\n\n7. **Post Your Answer**: Tap the \"Post\" button to submit your answer anonymously.\n\nYour answer will now be posted without your name or profile being associated with it. Note that even though your identity is hidden, Quora moderators can still see who posted the answer to ensure the platform\u2019s guidelines are followed.",
